      Energy efficiency

      As certified by
      ECOLOGO

      ECOLOGO

      ECOLOGO certified products are made with materials that reduce environmental impact at one or more stages of their life cycle, from raw materials to end of life. An ECOLOGO certification indicates that a product has met environmental performance standards, which include criteria in some or all of the following categories: materials, energy, manufacturing and operations, health and environment, product performance and use, and product stewardship and innovation. Products are evaluated on the applicable criteria through testing and auditing.

      Learn more about this certification
      EPEAT

      EPEAT

      EPEAT certifies electronic products based on sustainability impacts across their life cycle including requirements for energy efficiency and end-of-life management. An EPEAT registered product can also meet optional more ambitious criteria including reduction of fluorinated greenhouse gases (F-GHGs). Products meeting 50% - 74% optional criteria are 'Silver' and those meeting 75% or more are 'Gold'.

      Learn more about this certification

      Galaxy S25 Ultra handles the small details so you can focus on staying in the moment. Get several tasks fulfilled with one simple ask, and get insightful tips throughout your day to stay one step ahead. Simplify life with AI that evolves with you to work better for you.

      Compatible with select apps. Requires Google Gemini account. Results may vary based on input; check responses for accuracy. Displays daily select information from select apps (some apps may require internet connection). Compatible with common video formats accessible in Gallery; helps minimize six sounds (Voice/speech, Music, Noise, Crowd, Nature, Wind). Utilizes AI; results vary. As compared to Galaxy S24 Ultra. Requires screen resolution setting to QHD+. Galaxy AI features track data and require a compatible Galaxy wearable device (sold separately), Samsung Health app and Samsung account. Galaxy AI features track data and require a compatible Galaxy wearable device (sold separately), Samsung Health app and Samsung account. Galaxy Al basic features provided by Samsung are free.       How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Flagship Brains, FE Price Incredible 2025 Value
      Flagship Brains, FE Price Incredible 2025 Value Samsung S25 FE Review: The Smartest Affordable Doesnt Feel Affordable I upgraded to the Samsung Galaxy S25 FE 256GB (Unlocked, 2025) and it instantly proved that FE no longer means the budget cousin. It delivers a flagship-style experience powered by actual intelligence. The display is bright, sharp, and smooth, making everything from doom-scrolling to spreadsheets look unfairly good. The 256GB storage is perfect for heavy app users and photo hoarders like me plenty of space, zero cloud-panicked storage math. Performance-wise, this phone is a multitasking ninja. I run work apps, streaming, navigation, and background downloads, and it handles everything without drama, lag, or turning into a pocket heater. The AI features genuinely help too smart photo enhancement, writing suggestions, and adaptive system tweaks that make everyday use feel faster and more intuitive. The unlocked flexibility is a huge bonus carrier switching, travel SIMs, or no SIM at all, it just works. Battery life? Solid. It gets me through the day with space to spare, even with heavier 5G and app usage. Pros: Fast and smooth performance for daily tasks AI features are actually useful (not salesperson poetry) 256GB storage = generous and practical Slim, modern FE design looks premium Handles 5G and accessories reliably Unlocked freedom is clutch No bloat-feeling slowdown so far Cons / Tips: Not the absolute top-tier S line but honestly, unless you stare at spec sheets for sport, youll never feel like you compromised. Pair with a good USB-C GaN Charger if you want maximum fast-charging efficiency. Because its FE-light and sleek, consider a grippy magnetic case if you like snap-on accessories. Bottom line: If you want a phone that delivers flagship thinking, amazing everyday performance, and smart storage value without flagship pricing guilt, this is your 2025 sweet spot. The S25 FE earns 5 stars not because its affordable but because it never makes you think about the word affordable at all.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice Phone---Have Patience!!!!!
        Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2026
        Color: WhiteSize: 128GBStyle: S25 FEPattern Name: Phone OnlyVerified Purchase
        This is a very nice phone at a reasonable price. Usually, the "FE" designation just means the body of the phone is plastic rather than metal. This phone works just as well as the S25 and will serve most users quite well.
        The 128 GB storage will hold thousands of pictures, etc. and all pictures and data can be transferred to one's computer if the memory should fill-up. If you go to the two SIM card upgrade you will pay much more for the phone for not that much more "bang for the buck".
        Remember, this phone will work just fine for the MAJORITY of people who just want great calling, texting and photo abilities.
        The camera does a very nice job and is quite versatile. You can do most everything you need for picture taking.
        One "little" problem however, you better know what you are doing if you plan to link/connect via bluetooth to your car hands-free system. Connection takes "patience". However, stick with it for once you do get connected the connection is very solid, clear and fast. If it would be helpful, my car is a 2024 Jeep Grand Cherokee Limited with the UConnect-5 System in it. It took a little bit of "wrestling" to get the connection made but it will eventually got through.
        The phone feels very good in the hand and it does have metal banding/edges all around it. Definitely get a screen protector and some form of body case for added safety. The phone works just fine with a screen protector on it because you can increase touch sensitivity through the phone settings.
        Take your time setting this phone up. It has a "thousand" menus and selections that make the phone very personalized for each person. Before doing the set up I would suggest you go online and look at many of the tutorials that are offered on set up and use.
        The phone is completely unlocked for ANY United States Carrier. All you may need is a new SIM card to be sure you get the company services you want. These SIM cards can be obtained at the various carrier's stores--they cost about $10.00 and the technicians will install them for you. These phones WILL allow you to use the new eSIM card set-ups also.
        I would recommend purchase of this Samsung S25FE phone for certain! It is a great buy and should give you many years of service.
